# Selenium Dropdown Automation Project

This project demonstrates how to handle **dropdowns using Selenium WebDriver in Java** with the `Select` class and how navigation (refresh) affects dropdown selection.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used
- Java
- Selenium WebDriver
- ChromeDriver
- Maven (optional)
- TestAutomationPractice Website

---

## üìÇ Project Structure

---

## üöÄ What This Script Does
1. Launches Chrome browser
2. Opens the test site:  
   https://testautomationpractice.blogspot.com/
3. Selects **Canada** from dropdown
4. Refreshes the page
5. Selects **France** from dropdown again

---

## üíª Source Code

```java
package newChallange;

import java.time.Duration;
import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.Select;

public class dropdowns {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
        driver.manage().window().maximize();
        driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(Duration.ofSeconds(10));

        driver.get("https://testautomationpractice.blogspot.com/");

        Select dropdown = new Select(driver.findElement(By.id("country")));
        dropdown.selectByVisibleText("Canada");

        driver.navigate().refresh();

        Select dropdown2 = new Select(driver.findElement(By.id("country")));
        dropdown2.selectByVisibleText("France");
    }
}
